original: Franck, Eskil Gerhard Daniel, komminister, Uddevalla, f. 3/6/10 i Ödsmål, Gbgs o. Boh. 1., av kontr :prost Ernst F. o. Elisabeth Ulff. G. 35 m. Margit Hagard. Barn: Elisabeth f. 37, Gunilla 42. — Stud:ex. i Gbg 28, teol. fil. ex. 29, teol. kand., prakt. teol. prov samt prästv. f. Gbgs iStift 33. Tjg. s. v. kommin. i Brastad o. öckerö samt s. pastorsadj. o. v. pastor i Bro, kommin. i öckerö 37, i Uddevalla fr. 47, SvRKftjt.
translated: Franck, Eskil Gerhard Daniel, vicar, Uddevalla, born June 3rd, 1910 in Ödsmål, Gothenburg and Bohus County, son of district dean Ernst F. and Elisabeth Ulff. Married to Margit Hagard in 1935. Children: Elisabeth, born in 1937, Gunilla, born in 1942. Completed his high school exam in Gothenburg in 1928, theological and philosophical exam in 1929, practical theological exam and ordained as a priest in the Diocese of Gothenburg in 1933. Served as vicar in Brastad and Öckerö and as pastoral assistant and vicar in Bro. Became vicar in Öckerö in 1937 and in Uddevalla from 1947. Member of the Swedish Church Assembly.
